## Runtime contract (must follow)
1. Build/install package from source checkout.
2. Install package into target project (`MBO_Alpha`) as end-user style dependency.
3. Run from target project with `npx mbo` (or `mbo` if globally installed).
4. Do NOT use `node /path/to/bin/mbo.js` for acceptance.

## Install/run commands
```bash
cd /Users/johnserious/MBO
scripts/mbo-install-alpha.sh /Users/johnserious/MBO_Alpha

cd /Users/johnserious/MBO_Alpha
npx mbo
```

For scripted E2E capture (dual-log output):
```bash
cd /Users/johnserious/MBO
scripts/alpha-runtime.sh e2e --alpha /Users/johnserious/MBO_Alpha
```

## E2E acceptance script (4 turns)
From `/Users/johnserious/MBO_Alpha`:
1. launch: `npx mbo`
2. input: `status`
3. input: `Run readiness-check workflow now and complete one full workflow cycle successfully in plain English.`
4. input: `go`
5. input: `approved`

